  "panels": [
    {
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 100,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "## HRIV Service Health\n\nStart here for **student-visible health first**: can users open images, are failures rising, and is request latency stable? Generic pod CPU/memory is kept lower on the dashboard on purpose.\n\n- Use **Component** to focus on the backend/runtime slice that emitted the telemetry.\n- Use **User role** to separate broad student impact from instructor/admin activity.\n- Zero traffic can be normal during idle periods; treat synthetic monitoring and explicit failures as the primary availability signal.\n\nEvery selector exposed on this dashboard is wired into at least one panel query so the filter bar always changes the view operators are looking at.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.0.0",
      "title": "Scope & drill-down",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Scope, caveats, and drill-down guidance for this dashboard."
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${loki}"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "lineWidth": 1,
            "showPoints": "never",
            "stacking": {
              "group": "A",
              "mode": "none"
            }
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "noValue": "No matching image-view activity"
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "failed"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "red",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 5
      },
      "id": 8,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [],
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom",
          "showLegend": true
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "none"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${loki}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(count_over_time({service_name=~\"${component}\"} | event_name=\"image.view.ready\" | event_synthetic!=\"true\" | user_role=~\"${user_role}\" [$__auto]))",
          "legendFormat": "successful",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${loki}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(count_over_time({service_name=~\"${component}\"} | event_name=\"image.view.failed\" | event_synthetic!=\"true\" | user_role=~\"${user_role}\" [$__auto]))",
          "legendFormat": "failed",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Image views vs failures",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "description": "Student-visible image-open outcome from structured telemetry. This is the quickest way to see whether users can actually open images, independent of generic API traffic."
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${loki}"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
